<l>palcāṉ ṟīrē palcāṉ ṟīrē</l>
<l>celkeṉac collā toḻikeṉa vilakkum</l>
<l>pollāc cūḻccip palcāṉ ṟīrē</l>
<l>yaṇilvari koṭuṅkāy vāḷpōḻn tiṭṭa</l>
<l>kāḻpō ṉalviḷar naṟuney tīṇṭā</l>
<l>taṭaiyiṭaik kiṭanta kaipiḻi piṇṭam</l>
<l>veḷḷeṭ cāntoṭu puḷippey taṭṭa</l>
<l>vēḷai ventai valci yākap</l>
<l>paraṟpey paḷḷip pāyiṉṟu vatiyu</l>
<l>muyavaṟ peṇṭirē mallē mātō</l>
<l>peruṅkāṭṭup paṇṇiya karuṅkōṭ ṭīma</l>
<l>numakkari tākuka tilla vemakkem</l>
<l>peruntōṭ kaṇavaṉ māynteṉa varumpaṟa</l>
<l>vaḷḷita ḻaviḻnta tāmarai</l>
<l>naḷḷirum poykaiyun tīyumō raṟṟē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l> You who are worthy of much [praise], you who are worthy of much [praise], (1)</l>
<l>with bad counsel, who block block [me], saying “stay behind”, </l>
<l>without saying “you may go”, you who are worthy of much [praise]: (2f.)</l>
<l>are we not women capable of surviving/suffering women (10)</l>
<l>who as of today remain on mats/without mats as a bed, strewn with pebbles, (9)</l>
<l>while [our] food is something boiled of Vēḷai, (8)</l>
<l>that is cooked, pouring tamarind with a paste of white sesame (7)</l>
<l>on rice balls pressed with the hand which lie on a leaf, (6)</l>
<l>not touched by fragrant ghee, very white like the kernels (5)</l>
<l>that were cleaved by a sword from a curved unripe fruit striped [like] a squirrel? (4)</l>
<l>The pyre with [its] black peak prepared in the vast cremation ground, (11)</l>
<l>let it be difficult/precious for you. For us, (12)</l>
<l>because our big-shouldered husband is gone, (13a-c)</l>
<l>the fire and the centre of the big pond (15a-c)</l>
<l>with lotuses that open [their] pointed petals so that the buds end (13c+14)</l>
<l>	are but one. (15d)</l>
</lg>
